
segments ['Physics is the study of matter, energy, and their interactions. It seeks to understand the fundamental laws governing the universe.\n', '\n1. Physics explores the basic building blocks of reality, from subatomic particles to cosmic structures.\n\n---CODE---\n\nclass GeneratedScene(Scene):\n    def construct(self):\n        title = Text("Physics: From Tiny to Huge").scale(1.2)\n        self.play(Write(title))\n        self.wait(1)\n        \n        small = Text("Subatomic Particles").scale(0.8).to_edge(LEFT)\n        large = Text("Cosmic Structures").scale(0.8).to_edge(RIGHT)\n        \n        self.play(title.animate.to_edge(UP))\n        self.play(Write(small), Write(large))\n        \n        arrow = Arrow(small, large)\n        self.play(GrowArrow(arrow))\n        \n        self.wait(2)\n        self.play(FadeOut(title), FadeOut(small), FadeOut(large), FadeOut(arrow))\n', '\n2. It investigates forces, motion, and energy, explaining phenomena from simple mechanics to complex quantum behaviors.\n\n---CODE---\n\nclass GeneratedScene(Scene):\n    def construct(self):\n        force = Text("Force").scale(0.8)\n        motion = Text("Motion").scale(0.8)\n        energy = Text("Energy").scale(0.8)\n        \n        triangle = Triangle().scale(2)\n        \n        self.play(Create(triangle))\n        self.play(Write(force.next_to(triangle, UP)))\n        self.play(Write(motion.next_to(triangle, DOWN + LEFT)))\n        self.play(Write(energy.next_to(triangle, DOWN + RIGHT)))\n        \n        self.wait(1)\n        \n        quantum = Text("Quantum Behavior").scale(0.8).to_edge(RIGHT)\n        arrow = Arrow(triangle, quantum)\n        \n        self.play(Create(arrow), Write(quantum))\n        \n        self.wait(2)\n        self.play(FadeOut(triangle), FadeOut(force), FadeOut(motion), FadeOut(energy), FadeOut(arrow), FadeOut(quantum))\n', '\n3. Physics uses mathematical models and experimental observations to describe and predict natural phenomena, from everyday experiences to the mysteries of the cosmos.\n\n---CODE---\n\nclass GeneratedScene(Scene):\n    def construct(self):\n        equation = Text("E = mcÂ²").scale(1.5)\n        self.play(Write(equation))\n        self.wait(1)\n        \n        telescope = Circle().scale(0.5).next_to(equation, LEFT)\n        self.play(Create(telescope))\n        \n        atom = Circle().scale(0.3).next_to(equation, RIGHT)\n        electron = Dot().move_to(atom.get_center())\n        self.play(Create(atom), Create(electron))\n        \n        self.play(electron.animate.rotate(TAU, about_point=atom.get_center()), run_time=2)\n        \n        self.wait(1)\n        self.play(FadeOut(equation), FadeOut(telescope), FadeOut(atom), FadeOut(electron))']
